attributedDescription.content:
The Boston Celtics dominated the Dallas Mavericks in game 1 of the 2024 NBA Finals, with Kristaps Porzingis shooting lights out in his minutes. The Dallas Mavericks have been a switch-heavy team on the defensive end, forcing opposing big men to punish those mismatches, and up to this point, teams haven't been able to do that. But the Boston Celtics looks like they've found their switch beater in Kristaps Porzingis.

Seeing all the success that he's having really makes you wonder how the Boston Celtics were able to pull off the Kristaps Porzingis trade in the first place. The Celtics have fully fleshed out their core around Jayson Tatum and Jaylen Brown, and with teams having their hands full defending those two, Porzingis really becomes the straw that stirs the drink.
